INSERT INTO `lang_base` VALUES ('_template','help_preferences','<small>\r\n\r\n<p>Personal Preferences allow you to modify the look and layout of ATutor to your liking.   Edit your preferences on the <img src=\"images/prefs.gif\" alt=\"Preferences icon\" /> <a href=\"users/preferences.php?g=12\">Preferences</a> page. Each of the preference settings are described briefly in this section. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Position Options</h3>\r\n<p><b>Menu </b>: position the menu on the left or right. You might prefer it on the left if you are left handed, or you might prefer it on the right, because it\'s close to your browser\'s scroll bar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Sequence Links</b>: The sequence arrows (or text links) can be positioned at the top or bottom of the page, or both top and bottom.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Table of Content</b>: Position the Contents menu either at the top of the content, or at the bottom. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Display Options</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Show Topic Numbering</b>: Enabling this preference will display topics in the menus and page headings with accompanying numbers (e.g. 2.3.2). You might enable numbering if you prefer the content numerically structured, or disable numbering to conserve space or reduce the screen clutter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Show Breadcrumbs</b>: Hide breadcrumb links that appear across the top of the content area if you don\'t find them useful. Show breadcrumbs if you like to know your hierarchical  location in the content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Show Heading Navigation</b>: Show heading navigation to display page headings as links to other pages higher up in the hierarchy of the content you are viewing.  Hide heading navigation to conserve space, or if you do not find it useful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Show ATutor Help</b>: ATutor help boxes provide basic information for using ATutor tools.  Show ATutor Help while you are learning to use ATutor. Hide ATutor Help if you are familiar with ATutor. When ATutor Help is hidden, the Help icons remain.  Toggle the help icons to open and close the help box for the page you are viewing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Show ATutor Popup Help</b>: Popup help is available through a small question mark icon [<img src=\"images/help3.gif\" align=\"middle\" alt=\"mini help icon\" height=\"15\" width=\"16\" />] next to a tool, and provide tips on getting the most effective use out of the tool. Show popup help while are mastering the ATutor tools. Hide popup help when you have become an ATutor guru.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Text and Icons</h3>\r\n<p><b>Member Navigation</b>: Display the Member Navigation bar with  icons and text if you prefer a text and graphic representation in the main tabs across the top of ATutor. Display icons only to conserve space, reduce screen clutter, or to display only graphic representations. Display text only for accessibility, or if you prefer text over icons.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Course Navigation</b>:  Display the Course Navigation bar with  icons and text if you prefer a text and graphic representation. Display icons only to conserve space, reduce screen clutter, or to display only graphic representations. Display text only for accessibility, or if you prefer text over icons.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Sequence Navigation</b>:  Display the Sequence Navigation arrows with icons and text if you prefer a text and graphic representation. Display icons only to conserve space, reduce clutter, or to display only graphic representations. Display text only for accessibility, or if you prefer text over icons.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Content Headings</b>:  Display the page headings with icons and text if you prefer a text and graphic representation. Display text only to conserve space, reduce clutter, or remove graphic representations. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Menu Options</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Each of the menu modules that appear in the ATutor Menu are optional. You may choose to include all of the menu modules in your menu configuration, or you may choose not to display any of them. You may also choose to order the modules in the order that suits you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You might choose the display the <strong>Local Menu</strong>, and hide the <strong>Global Menu</strong> if you prefer  to see the content listing in a smaller, lesson size display. Or, you might choose to display the Global Menu and hide the Local Menu, if you prefer to see the content for the entire course listed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You might choose to locate the <strong>Users Online</strong> module at the top of the menu so you can easily see the list of classmates currently online, and communicate with them either through your Inbox and private messaging, or though the Chat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You might choose to locate the <strong>Related Topics </strong>module at the top of the menu so you can see a list of other topics in the course related to the current one.\r\n\r\n<h3>Themes</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>New in 1.4!  The overall look and feel of your ATutor installation is controlled by the theme setting.  ATutor comes with a default theme, but your system administrator can add other options.  </p>\r\n\r\n</small>',NOW(),'');
